---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="about" description="Who is Niro Åhman">
  <a slot="back" href="/">&larr; ~/index</a>
  <main class="about">
    <div class="about-body">
      <div class="photo-col">
        <div class="photo-wrap">
          <img src="/niro.jpg" alt="Niro Åhman" class="photo" />
        </div>
        <p class="photo-caption">niro.åhman — Akaa, Finland</p>
      </div>

      <div class="text-col">
        <h1 class="name glow">Niro Åhman</h1>
        <p class="role">Senior Full-Stack Developer</p>

        <p class="bio">
          I'm a deep-stack developer with a decade of experience. The kind where you start out
          writing C++ Linux drivers for 5G radios at Nokia, move on to building secure,
          national-scale systems for the medical and national security sectors, and somehow end up
          building smart office UIs that run on kiosk screens around the world.
        </p>

        <p class="bio">
          Most of this has happened from my underground basement office. It's the perfect spot for
          deep focus, but I'm definitely not a hermit. I genuinely enjoy interacting with people,
          bouncing ideas around and working in a smart hybrid setup.
        </p>

        <p class="bio">
          My core is in frontend architecture (React, Next.js, TypeScript), but the full picture has
          always interested me more than just the frontend slice. In my current role, I architected
          and delivered the UI for two hardware-integrated enterprise PWAs to production within a
          single year. When not doing that, I build and maintain a real-time, data-intensive IoT
          dashboard managing thousands of devices.
        </p>

        <p class="bio">
          Right now my focus is heavily on developer experience and agentic AI. I'm actively
          building multi-agent dev workflows and incorporating tools like Claude and Gemini into
          everything I do. Mostly because they are genuinely better at catching my mistakes than I
          am at making them.
        </p>

        <p class="bio">
          I do my best work in mature, trust-based engineering cultures where people actually give a
          damn and pull in the same direction. Whether that's fully remote or a hybrid model where
          we actually get together to solve problems, the best code always comes out of teams like
          that.
        </p>

        <p class="bio">
          When the laptop closes: wife, three daughters, tabletop games, slaying in PoE 2, and
          running a suspiciously large Farming Simulator operation. 🚜⚔️
        </p>

        <div class="stack">
          <p class="stack-label">current stack</p>
          <ul class="stack-list">
            <li>React / Next.js / TypeScript</li>
            <li>Go</li>
            <li>AWS (ECS, Lambda, RDS, S3)</li>
            <li>Postgres</li>
            <li>Docker / Proxmox</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="links">
          <a href="https://github.com/niroahman" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
            >github ↗</a
          >
          <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/niroahman" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
            >linkedin ↗</a
          >
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2rem 1.5rem;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
  }

  .about-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  .back {
    color: var(--phosphor-dim);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color 0.15s;
  }

  .back:hover {
    color: var(--phosphor);
  }

  .breadcrumb {
    color: var(--phosphor);
    opacity: 0.5;
  }

  .about-body {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 240px 1fr;
    gap: 3rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  /* ── Photo ── */
  .photo-col {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .photo-wrap {
    position: relative;
    width: 240px;
    height: 340px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .photo {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
    object-position: center -100px;
    display: block;
    filter: grayscale(1) contrast(1.1) brightness(0.95);
  }

  /* phosphor color tint */
  .photo-wrap::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: var(--phosphor);
    mix-blend-mode: color;
    opacity: 0.35;
    pointer-events: none;
    z-index: 1;
  }

  /* scanlines */
  .photo-wrap::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: repeating-linear-gradient(
      to bottom,
      transparent,
      transparent 2px,
      rgba(0 0 0 / 0.18) 2px,
      rgba(0 0 0 / 0.18) 4px
    );
    pointer-events: none;
    z-index: 2;
  }

  .photo-caption {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    color: var(--phosphor-dim);
    text-align: center;
  }

  /* ── Text ── */
  .name {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin: 0 0 0.25rem;
    font-weight: bold;
  }

  .role {
    color: var(--phosphor-dim);
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
  }

  .bio {
    color: var(--phosphor);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    opacity: 0.85;
  }

  .stack {
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    border-left: 2px solid var(--dim);
    padding-left: 1rem;
  }

  .stack-label {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    color: var(--phosphor-dim);
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  }

  .stack-list {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.25rem;
    color: var(--phosphor);
    opacity: 0.8;
  }

  .stack-list li::before {
    content: '> ';
    color: var(--phosphor-dim);
  }

  .links {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .links a {
    color: var(--phosphor-dim);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    transition: color 0.15s;
  }

  .links a:hover {
    color: var(--phosphor);
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .about-body {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .photo-wrap {
      width: 100%;
      height: 260px;
    }
  }
</style>
